OL,5, A doctor who was sacked for raising    
OL,6, patient safety concerns has won a case 
OL,7, against England's hospital regulator,  
OL,8, the Care Quality Commission (CQC).     
OL,10,FOrthopaedic surgeon Shyam Kumar worked 
OL,11,Fpart-time for the CQC as a special     
OL,12,Fadviser on hospital inspections, but   
OL,13,FManchester Employment Tribunal found   
OL,14,Fthat he was unfairly dismissed.        
OL,16,FHe had reported concerns regarding     
OL,17,Finadequate hospital inspections, staff 
OL,18,Fbullying and serious patient harm.     
OL,20,FThe CQC "accepted the findings".       
